1
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:17,233
I won't let my anger
take over me.

2
00:00:17,367 --> 00:00:21,133
I will put everything behind me.

3
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:24,000
I won't stand between you
and Red anymore.

4
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,533
I won't stop you
from loving him.

5
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:29,800
Even if you don't come back
to me anymore.

6
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:34,433
Come on, Red.
You're not even well yet.

7
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:36,067
And you want to see Eden
already?

8
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:37,667
Come on, just for once,
please...

9
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:39,933
The car's brake didn't work,
Dad.

10
00:00:40,067 --> 00:00:42,267
What do you mean?

11
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:44,000
We had an accident

12
00:00:44,133 --> 00:00:45,667
because the car's brake
didn't work.

13
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:46,933
- No.
- It's all my fault.

14
00:00:47,067 --> 00:00:48,400
- No, no, Son.
- It's my fault.

15
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:50,867
Red, no. Don't blame yourself.

16
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,467
It's a mechanical failure
if a car's brake doesn't work.

17
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:56,100
If she keeps this up,

18
00:00:56,233 --> 00:00:57,367
we can actually
have her discharged

19
00:00:57,500 --> 00:00:59,433
as early as maybe tomorrow.

20
00:00:59,567 --> 00:01:02,300
But we still need
to run a few more tests.

21
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:05,067
If she passes those,
then I can have her discharged.

22
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:07,733
Get your strength back,
and once you're well enough,

23
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:09,900
you can go and see Red.

24
00:01:10,033 --> 00:01:12,233
I won't stand in your way
anymore.

25
00:01:12,367 --> 00:01:14,167
The investigators
just informed me.

26
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:17,900
They found out that
the brake line was cut down,

27
00:01:18,033 --> 00:01:20,000
- which caused the accident.
- What?

28
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:21,033
Looks like someone did it
on purpose.

29
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:23,233
Eden and Red
were not the targets.

30
00:01:23,367 --> 00:01:25,100
You were the target, Amanda.

31
00:01:25,233 --> 00:01:27,533
This is the answer
to all your questions.

32
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:28,633
It's Zandro.

33
00:01:31,733 --> 00:01:32,767
Talk!

34
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:33,900
Bastards!

35
00:01:35,167 --> 00:01:37,467
He probably doesn't know
his line yet.

36
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:38,467
That's enough!

37
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:40,433
You don't need to hurt him.

38
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,533
I don't know
what you're talking about.

39
00:01:42,667 --> 00:01:45,333
How many times
did Rina abandon you?

40
00:01:45,467 --> 00:01:47,667
Do you think
she won't do it again?

41
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:49,867
Your sister is just using you.

42
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,833
Are you going to let her
get away with it?

43
00:01:53,967 --> 00:01:57,000
Mommy Rina is to blame
for our accident?

44
00:01:57,133 --> 00:01:59,933
Zandro confessed
that Rina told him to do it.

45
00:02:00,067 --> 00:02:01,433
But I don't think

46
00:02:01,567 --> 00:02:03,433
they're capable
of doing that, Mom.

47
00:02:03,567 --> 00:02:07,400
Here. It's the CCTV footage.

48
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:11,000
What is this video
supposed to mean?

49
00:02:11,133 --> 00:02:12,400
Your son had an accident

50
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:15,067
because of what your wife
and her brother did.

51
00:02:15,233 --> 00:02:19,333
Rina told Zandro
to cut my car's brake line.

52
00:02:19,467 --> 00:02:22,200
But your son ended up
getting hurt.

53
00:02:22,333 --> 00:02:26,767
You're the reason why Yenyen
and I had an accident.

54
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:31,267
Eden's family is doing this
to ruin us.

55
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,567
They're just accusing me.

56
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:33,767
It's not true.

57
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:35,033
That's enough!

58
00:02:35,167 --> 00:02:38,600
The CCTV footage is not lying.

59
00:02:38,733 --> 00:02:40,933
And Amanda is not lying, either.

60
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:42,000
It's you!

61
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:45,200
You're the one who's lying!

62
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:46,600
Victor.

63
00:02:46,733 --> 00:02:47,700
Victor.

64
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:58,333
Excuse me.

65
00:02:58,467 --> 00:03:01,067
We have a warrant of arrest
for Mrs. Rina Ramos.

66
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:03,467
- Why?
- For trying to kill

67
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:06,933
Mrs. Amanda Madrigal
and Miss Eden Sta. Maria.

68
00:03:07,067 --> 00:03:08,733
That's not true.
I didn't do anything.

69
00:03:08,867 --> 00:03:09,767
I'm innocent.

70
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:11,367
I'm not coming with you.

71
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:12,467
I'm not coming.

72
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:15,033
Ma'am, your brother,
Mr. Zandro Lucero,

73
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:17,433
has confessed already.

74
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:18,500
He's lying!

75
00:03:18,633 --> 00:03:19,633
That's not true!

76
00:03:19,767 --> 00:03:21,300
I'm not coming with you.

77
00:03:21,467 --> 00:03:23,100
I'm not coming!

78
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:26,533
Victor! Come on!
I'm not coming with you!

79
00:03:26,667 --> 00:03:29,200
- Victor.
- Sorry, Rina. Go.

80
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:30,433
- Red.
- Go.

81
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:32,500
I didn't do anything.

82
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:34,433
I'm innocent.

83
00:03:34,567 --> 00:03:35,667
I didn't do anything wrong!

84
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,867
I'm not coming with you.

85
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,667
Victor!

86
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,833
Red!

87
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,267
- Take her.
- Victor!

88
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:03,633
Get your filthy hands off me!

89
00:04:03,767 --> 00:04:05,100
Don't touch me.

90
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,867
I know what to do.
I'm going to sit down.

91
00:04:12,567 --> 00:04:13,700
What?

92
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:15,367
Are you happy now?

93
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:17,600
You think you've won?

94
00:04:17,733 --> 00:04:18,700
Whatever!

95
00:04:19,767 --> 00:04:22,033
Whatever is going on
with your life

96
00:04:22,167 --> 00:04:23,400
is all your doing.

97
00:04:23,533 --> 00:04:25,667
You did that to yourself.

98
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:28,500
I didn't come here
to pick a fight with you.

99
00:04:28,667 --> 00:04:32,867
I'm here to bid you farewell.

100
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,133
And this is my gift to myself.

101
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:38,233
Our feud ends here.

102
00:04:38,367 --> 00:04:40,367
Because you will pay

103
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:44,000
for everything you've done
to Eden and me.

104
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,600
Yes.

105
00:04:46,733 --> 00:04:50,200
And I want to move on
with my life.

106
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:53,733
I want to unload all
the heavy baggage in my life.

107
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,400
Rina,

108
00:04:57,967 --> 00:04:59,367
I forgive you.

109
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:04,033
So, bon voyage,

110
00:05:04,167 --> 00:05:06,667
and you can rot in hell!

111
00:05:10,567 --> 00:05:11,933
You're a wench, Amanda!

112
00:05:13,167 --> 00:05:16,367
Beast!
This is not over yet, Amanda!

113
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:19,533
You will pay!

114
00:05:19,667 --> 00:05:21,100
You will pay for this!

115
00:05:21,367 --> 00:05:23,333
All of you will pay for this!

116
00:05:23,467 --> 00:05:25,600
This is not over yet, Amanda!

117
00:05:25,733 --> 00:05:27,900
- We're not done yet!
 - Shut up!

118
00:05:28,033 --> 00:05:30,067
You're a monster, Amanda!

119
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:31,567
Beast!

120
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,967
Mom, where are we going?

121
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:41,967
I'm sure you'll be happy
where I'm taking you.

122
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:26,800
Red!

123
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,633
Red, I thought
I wouldn't see you again

124
00:07:29,767 --> 00:07:32,033
after the car accident.

125
00:07:32,167 --> 00:07:34,067
I thought it was the end
of everything.

126
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,233
That's not going to happen.

127
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:40,367
We survived the island.

128
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:42,633
We survived our family's feud.

129
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:46,900
No one can separate us now.

130
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:55,733
Miss Amanda, thank you
for letting us see each other.

131
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:57,033
Thank you, Red.

132
00:07:57,167 --> 00:08:01,267
You've proved
how much you love Eden.

133
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:05,067
And I saw how happy she is
when she's with you.

134
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:08,933
Who am I to stand in the way
of your happiness?

135
00:08:10,933 --> 00:08:11,900
Red,

136
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:15,700
please forgive me.

137
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:17,967
I didn't see it before.

138
00:08:21,233 --> 00:08:22,633
Forgive me...

139
00:08:24,667 --> 00:08:26,300
for everything I've done.

140
00:08:33,033 --> 00:08:34,667
Thank you, Miss Amanda.

141
00:08:35,767 --> 00:08:38,867
It's enough to hear
you've accepted my relationship

142
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,233
with Yenyen.

143
00:08:42,733 --> 00:08:44,533
I'm overjoyed right now.

144
00:08:44,667 --> 00:08:45,933
Thank you.

145
00:08:47,067 --> 00:08:48,167
You can call me mom.

146
00:09:13,633 --> 00:09:16,100
Doesn't your dad
want to see me anymore?

147
00:09:20,333 --> 00:09:22,533
Are you both abandoning me?

148
00:09:24,300 --> 00:09:25,733
Dad doesn't want to see you.

149
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:30,533
Actually, he doesn't want me
to come and see you.

150
00:09:32,967 --> 00:09:34,667
But...

151
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,067
I can't do that to you.

152
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:38,500
You're my mother.

153
00:09:38,633 --> 00:09:39,600
I love you.

154
00:09:52,667 --> 00:09:54,133
Then do something, Red.

155
00:09:55,333 --> 00:09:56,733
Please, help me.

156
00:09:56,867 --> 00:09:57,967
Do something.

157
00:09:59,167 --> 00:10:01,933
The court's decision
will be released tomorrow.

158
00:10:03,567 --> 00:10:07,267
Please do something
to get me acquitted, Red.

159
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:10,400
Do you think
I haven't thought of that?

160
00:10:12,733 --> 00:10:15,033
If I do that,
it's like I'm enabling you.

161
00:10:15,167 --> 00:10:18,467
That I'm turning a blind eye
to your misdeed.

162
00:10:20,267 --> 00:10:22,000
But I did nothing wrong, Son.

163
00:10:22,133 --> 00:10:23,933
I didn't do anything wrong.

164
00:10:25,567 --> 00:10:27,000
Everything I did,

165
00:10:28,367 --> 00:10:29,500
I did for you

166
00:10:29,633 --> 00:10:31,100
and for your brother.

167
00:10:31,233 --> 00:10:32,633
I did for you
and for your brother.

168
00:10:32,767 --> 00:10:34,633
That's why it's hard for me.

169
00:10:36,167 --> 00:10:37,600
I'm suffering.

170
00:10:37,733 --> 00:10:40,233
Because I know
you did this out of love

171
00:10:40,367 --> 00:10:41,433
for my brother and me!

172
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:45,800
But you chose the wrong path,
Mom.

173
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:48,633
You tried to take a life, Mom.

174
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:51,367
A life.

175
00:10:55,233 --> 00:10:56,233
Mom, do you think...

176
00:10:57,933 --> 00:10:59,633
Do you think
this is not hard for me?

177
00:11:03,533 --> 00:11:05,800
I can see how you're suffering.

178
00:11:05,933 --> 00:11:07,167
It's hard for me, Mom.

179
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:09,200
It hurts.

180
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:13,700
I didn't dream of seeing this,
Mom.

181
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:16,033
I didn't dream of seeing you
in jail.

182
00:11:17,667 --> 00:11:19,700
Because all I want...

183
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:23,933
is to be with you
until I grow old.

184
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:29,833
I want you to be with my family.

185
00:11:29,967 --> 00:11:32,033
I want you to play with my kids.

186
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:36,967
But Mom, you have to pay
for what you've done.

187
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:38,767
- You have to pay for it.
- No!

188
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:40,200
I can't do anything to help you.

189
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:41,267
I'm sorry.

190
00:11:41,433 --> 00:11:43,667
- Red.
- This is hard for me.

191
00:11:46,933 --> 00:11:48,067
Red, it hurts!

192
00:11:49,267 --> 00:11:50,700
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, Mom.

193
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:52,433
I can't do anything to help you.

194
00:11:52,567 --> 00:11:54,633
You have to pay
for what you've done.

195
00:11:56,500 --> 00:12:00,500
It hurts to hear that
you're abandoning me, too, Red.

196
00:12:00,633 --> 00:12:01,867
Why?

197
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,133
Why, Red?

198
00:12:06,533 --> 00:12:08,033
I'm sorry, Mom.

199
00:12:08,167 --> 00:12:09,867
- I can't do anything.
- Red.

200
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,333
Red. Red, please.

201
00:12:11,467 --> 00:12:13,333
Red, please. Don't leave me.

202
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,133
Please, Red.

203
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,967
Don't leave me here.

204
00:12:19,100 --> 00:12:20,933
Don't do this to me, please.

205
00:12:21,067 --> 00:12:24,400
I didn't raise you
so you could abandon me.

206
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:26,667
Don't leave me here, Red.

207
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,567
Red, Red!

208
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:30,500
Help me, please.

209
00:12:31,567 --> 00:12:33,967
Red, help me, please.

210
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:36,067
Red!

211
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:38,300
Don't leave me here.

212
00:12:38,433 --> 00:12:40,833
Red, don't leave me.

213
00:12:40,967 --> 00:12:41,967
Red.

214
00:12:45,033 --> 00:12:47,100
Red, don't leave me here.

215
00:12:49,933 --> 00:12:51,033
Red!

216
00:12:52,533 --> 00:12:53,533
Red!

217
00:13:06,933 --> 00:13:08,133
Red, don't leave me.

218
00:13:08,267 --> 00:13:09,300
Red!

219
00:13:09,433 --> 00:13:10,400
Red!

220
00:13:10,533 --> 00:13:11,533
Red, please.

221
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:17,233
Red. Don't leave me here, Red!

222
00:13:18,733 --> 00:13:20,800
Red!

223
00:13:20,933 --> 00:13:23,367
Don't leave me here.

224
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:28,800
Red, don't leave me, Red.

225
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:34,033
Red, I love you.

226
00:13:34,167 --> 00:13:36,767
Don't leave me.

227
00:13:38,100 --> 00:13:40,400
Don't leave me, Red.

228
00:13:41,733 --> 00:13:43,867
I heard the two of you
are finally getting married.

229
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:47,400
Hopefully, there won't be
hindrances this time.

230
00:13:47,533 --> 00:13:49,533
Unless you're going to stop us.

231
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,767
No, Yenyen.

232
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:55,667
I've accepted that Red and I
are just meant to be friends.

233
00:13:56,933 --> 00:13:58,500
You are really the one for him.

234
00:13:59,533 --> 00:14:00,500
Thank you, Sab.

235
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:04,233
It's the least I can do
after all I've done.

236
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:07,500
I am genuinely happy
for both of you.

237
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:17,867
Sab, we have to go.
They're waiting for us.

238
00:14:19,033 --> 00:14:22,033
Oh, I should wish
the two of you well.

239
00:14:23,033 --> 00:14:25,333
- Thank you.
- Take care of Sab.

240
00:14:25,467 --> 00:14:26,800
You take care of Colby, too.

241
00:14:32,467 --> 00:14:35,433
Bro, this is my first payment
for my loan.

242
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:38,367
You don't need to do this, Bro.

243
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:41,433
Especially now
that we're going to be family.

244
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:44,833
Loans should be paid, Lucho.

245
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:46,133
I can't forget about that.

246
00:14:47,933 --> 00:14:50,233
Victor, how is Red doing?

247
00:14:51,733 --> 00:14:54,600
How is he taking
Rina's situation?

248
00:14:54,733 --> 00:14:57,367
I know he's having a hard time.

249
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,833
He loves his mother.

250
00:15:01,867 --> 00:15:03,800
Should I drop the case
against her?

251
00:15:05,433 --> 00:15:06,533
No.

252
00:15:07,867 --> 00:15:12,167
Rina has to learn her lesson.

253
00:15:13,967 --> 00:15:14,933
Even if it's hard,

254
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,767
Red and I accepted
our circumstances.

255
00:15:19,067 --> 00:15:20,200
Because that's the right thing
to do.

256
00:15:22,667 --> 00:15:23,767
In a few days,

257
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,533
her sentence will be released.

258
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,367
Once that happens,

259
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:32,333
she will be transferred
to women's correctional.

260
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:42,200
Bro, are you a newbie?

261
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:43,367
I haven't seen you before.

262
00:15:59,233 --> 00:16:02,033
Ma'am, here are your belongings
from Mr. Akashi.

263
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:09,133
Tell him...

264
00:16:10,467 --> 00:16:11,533
I said thank you.

265
00:16:28,933 --> 00:16:30,833
Mr. Akashi wants you
to have this, Ma'am.

266
00:16:32,067 --> 00:16:33,067
Thank you.

267
00:16:45,533 --> 00:16:48,733
I can't miss your wedding, Son.

268
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:57,767
That's why I prepared
something big for you.

269
00:16:59,667 --> 00:17:01,367
Express delivery.

270
00:17:02,867 --> 00:17:04,067
The Rina way.

271
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:09,567
Red?

272
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:17,000
Who are you?

273
00:17:17,133 --> 00:17:18,100
Chloe?

274
00:17:20,333 --> 00:17:21,467
Chloe!

275
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:22,667
Wait!

276
00:17:23,867 --> 00:17:24,900
Chloe!

277
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,900
Eden, what happened to you?

278
00:17:31,233 --> 00:17:32,267
Raichu, there's a dead baby.

279
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,367
She's covered in blood.

280
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:35,867
What are you talking about?

281
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:38,967
I'm not kidding.

282
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:39,967
A woman is holding her.

283
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:42,367
The baby's dead.
She's bleeding everywhere!

284
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:46,000
Eden, you're just having
a nightmare.

285
00:17:46,133 --> 00:17:48,700
You just woke up.

286
00:17:48,867 --> 00:17:50,700
My gosh, Eden.

287
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,033
There's no woman here.

288
00:17:52,167 --> 00:17:53,133
No baby.

289
00:17:53,267 --> 00:17:55,100
Nothing!

290
00:17:55,233 --> 00:17:58,833
Okay? So get ready
because today is your wedding.

291
00:17:58,967 --> 00:18:00,600
You need to get ready.
It's your wedding day.

292
00:18:00,733 --> 00:18:02,433
Go back to reality.

293
00:18:02,567 --> 00:18:03,933
It's your wedding,
and you've been thinking

294
00:18:04,067 --> 00:18:05,867
about horrible things.

295
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,167
It seemed so real.

296
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:10,967
Eden, you're being paranoid.

297
00:18:11,100 --> 00:18:14,967
Because Rina is still at large.

298
00:18:15,100 --> 00:18:17,133
What are you thinking?

299
00:18:17,267 --> 00:18:18,867
That she will do something bad
to you?

300
00:18:20,233 --> 00:18:22,400
I'm afraid of what could happen.

301
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:25,600
She might cause us trouble
again.

302
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:30,133
What if that dream
is telling us something?

303
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:32,533
What if she causes trouble?

304
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:43,400
I'm so glad that you came, Sab.

305
00:18:43,533 --> 00:18:45,500
I really appreciate it.

306
00:18:45,633 --> 00:18:47,767
Well, it's just my way
of proving to you

307
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:51,733
I'm really genuinely happy
for you and Yenyen.

308
00:18:52,833 --> 00:18:55,600
I'm no match for destiny.

309
00:18:57,833 --> 00:18:59,400
But seriously,

310
00:18:59,533 --> 00:19:00,467
how are you two doing?

311
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:02,267
Are you guys okay?

312
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,767
Especially you.

313
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:06,433
You're getting married, and...

314
00:19:06,567 --> 00:19:08,067
Aunt Rina's not here.

315
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:11,567
You know what I mean.
What if she...

316
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:13,867
I don't want to think about that
for now, Sab.

317
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:16,233
Well, of course,
it's hard for me.

318
00:19:16,367 --> 00:19:19,933
But I want her to get captured.

319
00:19:20,067 --> 00:19:22,167
I don't want her to get hurt.

320
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:24,067
I still care for her safety.

321
00:19:25,233 --> 00:19:28,200
But what if she comes back here?

322
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:32,933
My mom did a lot of bad things
to Yenyen and me.

323
00:19:33,067 --> 00:19:34,867
And I hate to say this, but,

324
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,133
if she tries to harm us
one more time...

325
00:19:36,267 --> 00:19:37,900
I might forget she's my mother.

326
00:19:39,167 --> 00:19:41,367
As of now,
I just want her to get caught.

327
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:43,967
I want her to pay
for all her crimes in jail.

328
00:19:45,133 --> 00:19:46,400
I understand.

329
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,300
There you go!
Your make-up looks perfect.

330
00:19:50,433 --> 00:19:51,600
You can put on your dress now.

331
00:20:28,167 --> 00:20:29,067
Hey.

332
00:20:30,033 --> 00:20:30,900
Eden!

333
00:21:01,867 --> 00:21:02,933
It's from Mommy Rina.

334
00:21:05,967 --> 00:21:07,233
What is it this time?

335
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:09,500
Raichu, this is from Mommy Rina.

336
00:21:11,267 --> 00:21:13,567
I'm sure it's her. She said
she had a surprise for me.

337
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:16,233
I don't get it.

338
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:19,500
Raichu, she's here.

339
00:21:19,633 --> 00:21:21,300
She's going to cause us trouble
again!

340
00:21:24,933 --> 00:21:26,233
She can't do this to us.

341
00:21:27,267 --> 00:21:28,567
I'm going to find her.

342
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:29,900
Hey.

343
00:21:30,033 --> 00:21:31,067
Eden!

344
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:42,233
Yen.

345
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,300
Yen.

346
00:21:43,433 --> 00:21:44,300
- Where is she going?
- Raichu,

347
00:21:44,433 --> 00:21:45,567
where is she going?

348
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:51,667
I don't know.

349
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,867
She said she saw your mom.

350
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,700
- Yen!
- Aunt Rina?

351
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:00,567
Yen, what are you doing there?

352
00:22:00,700 --> 00:22:01,700
Come back here.

353
00:22:19,233 --> 00:22:20,800
Are you okay?

354
00:22:20,933 --> 00:22:21,900
Sit down.

355
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,133
I saw your mom, Red.

356
00:22:26,267 --> 00:22:27,500
What?

357
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:29,667
She said she had a surprise
for us.

358
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:31,367
I know she won't leave us alone.

359
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:32,633
She's going to cause a scene.

360
00:22:32,767 --> 00:22:34,400
We have to stop her, Red.

361
00:22:37,667 --> 00:22:40,600
What if she just planned this
to make us come back to her?

362
00:22:42,833 --> 00:22:43,833
Red.

363
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:49,333
Yen,

364
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:51,067
don't worry.

365
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:53,333
Let the police do their job.

366
00:22:54,533 --> 00:22:57,467
I promise you
she won't be able to hurt you.

367
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,067
Or any member of my family.

368
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:02,900
I promise you,
my mom can't harm us.

369
00:23:03,033 --> 00:23:04,367
Any member of my family.

370
00:23:05,500 --> 00:23:06,900
I promise you that.

371
00:23:07,033 --> 00:23:08,067
She won't be able to find you.

372
00:23:33,233 --> 00:23:36,633
Oh my gosh! It's so gorgeous!

373
00:23:36,767 --> 00:23:38,000
Oh my God, Amanda.

374
00:23:38,133 --> 00:23:40,167
Eden, after everything
we've been through,

375
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:42,133
I just want to be a part
of this beautiful moment

376
00:23:42,267 --> 00:23:45,067
- in your life.
- I know this day

377
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:47,833
is very special for all of you,
Red.

378
00:23:47,967 --> 00:23:50,367
It's your wedding day.

379
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:52,967
Red, Eden,

380
00:23:54,633 --> 00:23:57,067
your child is not dead.

381
00:23:57,233 --> 00:23:59,567
You came to visit me
empty-handed.

382
00:23:59,700 --> 00:24:01,400
Come on, Red!

383
00:24:01,533 --> 00:24:03,400
We need something from you.

384
00:24:03,533 --> 00:24:04,667
From me?

385
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:05,967
Tell us the truth.

386
00:24:06,100 --> 00:24:07,367
Is our child still alive?
